name: .QB2012 File Extension
summary: Learn about .QB2012 files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: File created by the Mac version of QuickBooks money management software; can include company financial data, payroll information, and customer and employee data; often used for tracking small business finances; can be used for generating tax forms, invoices, payroll, and financial reports.

content: If you wish to migrate QuickBooks 2012 data to a Windows version of QuickBooks, export the file as a .QBB file by choosing File → Back Up to QuickBooks for Windows... and then import the QBB file into the Windows version of the software by choosing File → Open or Restore Company.
NOTE: Previous versions of QuickBooks for Mac use the extensions .QB2011, .QB2010, etc. However, these extensions are considered legacy since the QuickBooks 2012 release.
